budesonide for CD and UC; aminosalicylates for UC","Corticosteroids for UC only; budesonide for CD only; aminosalicylates for UC","Corticosteroids for CD and UC; budesonide for UC only; aminosalicylates for CD","Corticosteroids for UC only; budesonide for CD; aminosalicylates for CD and UC","Corticosteroids for CD only; budesonide for CD only; aminosalicylates for UC"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct treatment options for mild inflammatory bowel disease are as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroids for CD and UC; budesonide for CD and UC; aminosalicylates for UC\u003C/strong\u003E accurately reflects current treatment approaches\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESystemic corticosteroids are effective for both Crohn disease (CD) and ulcerative colitis (UC) in managing acute flares\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroids for UC only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as they are effective in both conditions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroids for CD and UC; budesonide for UC only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as budesonide can be used in both conditions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroids for UC only; budesonide for CD\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as both medications can be used in both conditions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroids for CD only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as they are beneficial in both CD and UC\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBudesonide is designed for targeted intestinal release and can be used in both CD and UC. Specifically, budesonide foam is used for active ulcerative colitis affecting the rectal and rectosigmoid colon, or for induction of remission in mild-to-moderate ulcerative colitis when 5-aminosalicylates are ineffective or not tolerated. Aminosalicylates are highly effective for UC but have limited evidence supporting their use in CD.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Corticosteroids are effective for both Crohn disease and ulcerative colitis","Budesonide can be used in both Crohn disease and ulcerative colitis due to its targeted intestinal release","Aminosalicylates are effective for ulcerative colitis but have limited benefit in Crohn disease"],"references":["Cai Z, Wang S, Li J. Treatment of Inflammatory Bowel Disease: A Comprehensive Review. Front Med (Lausanne). 2021 Dec 20;8:765474. doi: 10.3389/fmed.2021.765474. PMID: 34988090; PMCID: PMC8720971.","McDowell C, Farooq U, Haseeb M. Inflammatory Bowel Disease. 2023 Aug 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29262182","Fakhoury M, Negrulj R, Mooranian A, Al-Salami H. Inflammatory bowel disease: clinical aspects and treatments. J Inflamm Res. 2014 Jun 23;7:113-20. doi: 10.2147/JIR.S65979. PMID: 25075198; PMCID: PMC4106026","Tavakoli P, Vollmer-Conna U, Hadzi-Pavlovic D, Grimm MC. A Review of Inflammatory Bowel Disease: A Model of Microbial, Immune and Neuropsychological Integration. Public Health Rev. 2021 May 5;42:1603990. doi: 10.3389/phrs.2021.1603990. PMID: 34692176; PMCID: PMC8386758","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55288"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15392"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55288","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55288"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-12T20:10:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-12T20:11:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8083"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"